Subject: BUlbs and Corms
TextBody:
Hello again everyone,

 

Today at the garden workday several of us worked on Huston and Drea's old
driveway plot.  We dug up some of the dahlia and gladiola bulbs, or corms,
or rhizomes, whatever they are called. These are now officially property of
the garden.

 

They are in a rubber bucket in the shed.  Please help yourselves.  The light
brown potato like looking ones are the dahlias and they are still dormant.
The gladiolas are sprouting and they have a deep brown uniformly round bulb.
The gladiola leaves are blade like. 

 

There are likely more bulbs in the square bed closest to Suzanne's plot
(furthest from the olive trees) so if anyone is inclined they can dig more
up!

 

Francesca
HtmlBody:
Hello again everyone,

 

Today at the garden workday several of us worked on Huston and Drea's old driveway plot.  We dug up some of the dahlia and gladiola bulbs, or corms, or rhizomes, whatever they are called. These are now officially property of the garden.

 

They are in a rubber bucket in the shed.  Please help yourselves.  The light brown potato like looking ones are the dahlias and they are still dormant.  The gladiolas are sprouting and they have a deep brown uniformly round bulb.  The gladiola leaves are blade like. 

 

There are likely more bulbs in the square bed closest to Suzanne's plot (furthest from the olive trees) so if anyone is inclined they can dig more up!

 

Francesca
